{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tnmcy7U7hZhyRWbMraSLUE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-endpoint\n     3→description: Add a new REST API endpoint with view, URL route, schema, and test. Use when adding endpoints, routes, or API paths.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add Endpoint\n     7→\n     8→Add a complete API endpoint: view function, URL route, response schema, and test.\n     9→\n    10→## Usage\n    11→\n    12→```bash\n    13→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"view_name\": \"<name>\", \"url_path\": \"<path>\", \"url_name\": \"<name>\", \"schema_name\": \"<Schema>\", \"model_name\": \"<Model>\"}'\n    14→```\n    15→\n    16→If invoked as `/add-endpoint <view_name> <model_name>`:\n    17→\n    18→```bash\n    19→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"view_name\": \"$1\", \"url_path\": \"<inferred>\", \"url_name\": \"<inferred>\", \"schema_name\": \"<inferred>\", \"model_name\": \"$2\"}'\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→## Variables\n    23→\n    24→- **view_name**: View function name (e.g. `reservation_receipt`)\n    25→- **url_path**: URL path segment (e.g. `reservations/<int:pk>/receipt/`)\n    26→- **url_name**: URL name for reverse lookup (e.g. `reservation-receipt`)\n    27→- **schema_name**: Response schema class name (e.g. `ReceiptSchema`)\n    28→- **model_name**: Django model to query (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    29→\n    30→Extract these from the user's request. Infer url_path and url_name from view_name if not explicit.\n    31→\n    32→## Gotchas\n    33→\n    34→- If jig exits non-zero, it prints the rendered templates to stderr. Use that output to apply changes manually.\n    35→- Run `jig vars ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml` to confirm required variables if unsure.\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f629c47-22f5-463c-95f3-f9998278c84a","uuid":"53ecce14-8cea-4a9b-a6ab-a86ffc0c774f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y76FR9NftcrNqT5nNmb943","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from rest_framework.decorators import api_view\n     2→from rest_framework.response import Response\n     3→from .models import Reservation\n     4→\n     5→\n     6→@api_view([\"GET\"])\n     7→def reservation_list(request):\n     8→    reservations = Reservation.objects.all()\n     9→    return Response([{\"id\": r.id, \"guest\": r.guest_name} for r in reservations])\n    10→\n    11→\n    12→@api_view([\"GET\"])\n    13→def reservation_detail(request, pk):\n    14→    reservation = Reservation.objects.get(pk=pk)\n    15→    return Response({\n    16→        \"id\": reservation.id,\n    17→        \"guest\": reservation.guest_name,\n    18→        \"room\": reservation.room_number,\n    19→        \"status\": reservation.status,\n    20→    })\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f629c47-22f5-463c-95f3-f9998278c84a","uuid":"dcc1eaf4-afb7-4c63-82d7-44ce8587f2a1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W3qcDHWq9xXyrjCJHCVB5e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from django.urls import path\n     2→from . import views\n     3→\n     4→urlpatterns = [\n     5→    path(\"api/reservations/\", views.reservation_list, name=\"reservation-list\"),\n     6→    path(\"api/reservations/<int:pk>/\", views.reservation_detail, name=\"reservation-detail\"),\n     7→]\n     8→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f629c47-22f5-463c-95f3-f9998278c84a","uuid":"39171b3e-dfbd-4bd7-9213-1774a2c800f6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KAoCdXREX6kGyHagN28Trf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from rest_framework import serializers\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→class ReservationListSchema(serializers.Serializer):\n     5→    id = serializers.IntegerField()\n     6→    guest = serializers.CharField()\n     7→\n     8→\n     9→class ReservationDetailSchema(serializers.Serializer):\n    10→    id = serializers.IntegerField()\n    11→    guest = serializers.CharField()\n    12→    room = serializers.IntegerField()\n    13→    status = serializers.CharField()\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f629c47-22f5-463c-95f3-f9998278c84a","uuid":"dd4cef00-b55b-40ce-8fa3-bb15c0afbbeb"}
